    where  is any observable.
    This is a generalization of the relation between
    Schrodinger and Heisenberg pictures, and expresses
    the equivalence between active and passive
    views of symmetry transformations.
    If  is the generator of the transformation, then
    the infinitesimal transformation of the observable is
    .
    For normal (bosonic) symmetries, this of course implies that
    ,
    so invariance under the symmetry means the density matrix 
    commutes with the symmetry generator .
    But for an infinitesimal supersymmetry transformation,
    
    with  an external Grassmann spinor
    which anticommutes with all fermionic operators.
    In this case, one has
    







