independent from , , and .
No Abelian magnetic fields appear as hydrodynamic degrees
of freedom, since the gauge group of the theory is , not .
Moreover, holographic arguments imply that
the theory at non-zero temperature
has a mass gap,
in accord with the assumption
of finite correlation length made in Section .


